<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,824,1911]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,351,1017,1043]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">Distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="N. Ozhatay &amp; S. Demirci" authorityYear="2013" box="[388,506,1016,1042]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Muscari" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erdalii">
<emphasis box="[388,506,1016,1042]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">M. erdalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[683,767,1017,1043]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and distributed in the Mediterranean phytogeographical region. It grows on rocky slopes between at the elevation of 
<quantity box="[860,1019,1056,1082]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4144999999999999" metricValueMax="1.64" metricValueMin="1.189" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" unit="m" value="1414.5" valueMax="1640.0" valueMin="1189.0">
1189 
<emphasis box="[917,930,1057,1080]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">–</emphasis>
1640 m
</quantity>
a.s.l. and it is known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[151,202,1094,1120]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<figureCitation box="[312,384,1094,1120]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,255,793,816]" captionTargetBox="[171,1421,188,744]" captionTargetId="figure-130@7.[151,1436,176,769]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distrubution map of M. erdalii (stars), M. babachii (squares), and M. tenuiflorum (triangles) in Turkey." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100884/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,824,1911]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,333,1133,1159]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">Etymology</emphasis>
:—Named after Erdal Kaya, who is coordinator of Geophyte project and collector of the specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,824,1911]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,330,1211,1237]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">Karyology</emphasis>
:—Subgen. 
<taxonomicName box="[474,593,1210,1236]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Muscari" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Leopoldia">
<emphasis box="[474,593,1210,1236]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">Leopoldia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has two pairs of long, strongly heterobrachial chromosomes, clearly differentiated from three pairs of medium-sized chromosomes which may show slightly differences. There remain four pairs of small chromosomes. Some globose satellites may be found on either the short or the long arm. All Turkish species belonging to subgen. 
<taxonomicName box="[697,816,1325,1351]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Muscari" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Leopoldia">
<emphasis box="[697,816,1325,1351]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">Leopoldia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are diploid with 2n = 18 chromosomes (
<bibRefCitation author="Stuart, D. C." box="[1291,1432,1326,1352]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" pagination="189 - 196" refId="ref4238" refString="Stuart, D. C. (1970) Chromosome numbers in the genus Muscari Mill. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 30: 189 - 196." type="journal article" year="1970">Stuart 1970</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dalgic, G." box="[151,298,1365,1391]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" refId="ref3396" refString="Dalgic, G. (1990) Edirne ve Kirklareli Bolgesi Hyacinthaceae (Ornithogalum, Muscari, Bellevalia) Familyasi uzerinde Sitotaksonomik Arastirmalar, Phd. Thesis, Edirne University, 125 pp." type="book" year="1990">Dalgıç 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ozhatay, N. &amp; Johnson, M." box="[311,614,1365,1391]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" pagination="239 - 249" refId="ref3946" refString="Ozhatay, N. &amp; Johnson, M. (1996) Some karyological remarks on Turkish Allium sect. Allium, Bellevalia, Muscari, Ornithogalum subg. Ornithogalum. Bocconea 5: 239 - 249. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 4110233" type="journal article" year="1996">Özhatay &amp; Johnson 1996</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnson, M. &amp; Brandham, P. E." box="[626,952,1365,1391]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" pagination="121 - 138" refId="ref3740" refString="Johnson, M. &amp; Brandham, P. E. (1997) New chromosome numbers in petaloid monocotyledons and in other miscellaneous angiosperms. Kew Bulletin 52: 121 - 138." type="journal article" year="1997">Johnson &amp; Brandham 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ozhatay, N." box="[965,1135,1365,1391]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" pagination="237 - 240" refId="ref3996" refString="Ozhatay, N. (2000) Muscari Mill. In: Guner A., Ozhatay, N., Ekim, T. &amp; Canbaser, K., H. (eds.), Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands 11, suppl. Edinburgh University Press Edinburgh, 237 - 240 pp." type="book chapter" year="2000">Özhatay 2000</bibRefCitation>
). Also 
<taxonomicName authorityName="N. Ozhatay &amp; S. Demirci" authorityYear="2013" box="[1218,1335,1364,1390]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Muscari" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erdalii">
<emphasis box="[1218,1335,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">M. erdalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resulted diploid with 2n = 18 chromosomes, showing a karyotype closely related to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tausch" authorityYear="1841" box="[1164,1344,1403,1429]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Muscari" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuiflorum">
<emphasis box="[1164,1344,1403,1429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">M. tenuiflorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eker &amp; Koyuncu" authorityYear="2008" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Muscari" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="babachii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">M. babachii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,824,1911]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName authority=": The" authorityName="The" box="[198,375,1483,1510]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Muscari" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erdalii">
<emphasis box="[198,314,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">M. erdalii</emphasis>
: The
</taxonomicName>
karyotype formula is 2n = 2x = 18 = 
<quantity box="[816,853,1484,1510]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" unit="m" value="8.0">8m</quantity>
+ 4sm + 2st + 2st 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1064,1082,1481,1495]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">sat</superScript>
+ 
<quantity box="[1113,1139,1484,1510]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" unit="t" value="2.0">2t</quantity>
. Metaphase chromosome length ranges from 
<quantity box="[416,601,1523,1549]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" metricValueMax="6.6" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="4.2" valueMax="6.6" valueMin="1.8">1.8 to 6.6 µm</quantity>
; total haploid chromosome length is 
<quantity box="[1106,1216,1523,1549]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.73" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="17.3">17.3 µm</quantity>
±0.94 (
<figureCitation box="[1312,1421,1523,1549]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,255,1669,1692]" captionTargetBox="[163,1405,760,1598]" captionTargetId="figure-385@5.[151,1436,743,1645]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Karyotypes of M. erdalii (A), M. tenuiflorum (B) and M. babachii (C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100876" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100876/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Intrachromosomal asymmetry (M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[546,568,1577,1591]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">CA</subScript>
) is 36.79 and interchromosomal asymmetry index (CV 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1216,1236,1577,1591]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">CL</subScript>
) is 46.14.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,824,1911]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName authority=": The" authorityName="The" box="[198,435,1605,1632]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Muscari" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuiflorum">
<emphasis box="[198,374,1605,1631]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">M. tenuiflorum</emphasis>
: The
</taxonomicName>
karyotype formula is 2n = 2x = 18 = 
<quantity box="[879,916,1606,1632]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" unit="m" value="8.0">8m</quantity>
+ 6sm 
<superScript attach="left" box="[996,1014,1603,1617]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">sat</superScript>
+ 2st + 
<quantity box="[1112,1138,1606,1632]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" unit="t" value="2.0">2t</quantity>
. Metaphase chromosome length ranges from 
<quantity box="[416,601,1644,1670]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" metricValueMax="8.3" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="5.8" valueMax="8.3" valueMin="3.3">3.3 to 8.3 µm</quantity>
; total haploid chromosome length is 
<quantity box="[1107,1218,1644,1670]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.18" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="21.8">21.8 µm</quantity>
±0.61 (
<figureCitation box="[1314,1420,1644,1670]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,255,1669,1692]" captionTargetBox="[163,1405,760,1598]" captionTargetId="figure-385@5.[151,1436,743,1645]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Karyotypes of M. erdalii (A), M. tenuiflorum (B) and M. babachii (C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100876" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100876/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Intrachromosomal asymmetry (M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[546,568,1699,1713]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">CA</subScript>
) is 23.53 and interchromosomal asymmetry index (CV 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1216,1236,1699,1713]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">CL</subScript>
) is 36.60.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,824,1911]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName authority=": The" authorityName="The" box="[198,404,1727,1754]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Muscari" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="babachii">
<emphasis box="[198,340,1727,1753]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">M. babachii</emphasis>
: The
</taxonomicName>
karyotype formula is 2n = 2x = 18 = 
<quantity box="[855,892,1728,1754]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" unit="m" value="8.0">8m</quantity>
+ 6sm + 2st 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1042,1060,1724,1738]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">sat</superScript>
+ 
<quantity box="[1093,1115,1728,1754]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" unit="t" value="2.0">2t</quantity>
<superScript attach="right" box="[1116,1134,1724,1738]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">sat</superScript>
. Metaphase chromosome length ranges from 
<quantity box="[391,560,1766,1792]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6499999999999995" metricValueMax="9.7" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="6.6499999999999995" valueMax="9.7" valueMin="3.6">3.6 to 9.7 µm</quantity>
; total haploid chromosome length is 
<quantity box="[1017,1118,1766,1792]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.73" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="27.3">27.3 µm</quantity>
±0.43. Intrachromosomal asymmetry (M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[324,346,1821,1835]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">CA</subScript>
) is 28.57 and interchromosomal asymmetry index (CV 
<subScript attach="left" box="[994,1014,1821,1835]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">CL</subScript>
) is 38.36.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,824,1911]" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">
The chromosome number of 
<taxonomicName box="[544,686,1846,1872]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Muscari" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="babachii">
<emphasis box="[544,686,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">M. babachii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[704,795,1847,1873]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,255,1669,1692]" captionTargetBox="[163,1405,760,1598]" captionTargetId="figure-385@5.[151,1436,743,1645]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Karyotypes of M. erdalii (A), M. tenuiflorum (B) and M. babachii (C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100876" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100876/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
) and the chromosome number and morphology of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Muscari" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erdalii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">M. erdalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[244,336,1885,1911]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,255,1669,1692]" captionTargetBox="[163,1405,760,1598]" captionTargetId="figure-385@5.[151,1436,743,1645]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Karyotypes of M. erdalii (A), M. tenuiflorum (B) and M. babachii (C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100876" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100876/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
) are reported here for the first time.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5100869" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5100869" box="[151,938,2002,2025]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5100869/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="41" startId="3.[151,255,2002,2025]" targetBox="[151,1436,201,1902]" targetPageId="3">
